<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-04T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-04T23:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War/9–144:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-05T00:00:00-04:00">September
                                    5, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>7185. Referring to your telegrams 6953, August 26, 7 p.m.,<note n="89" xml:id="d58fn89">See footnote 88, <ref target="#pg_87">p.
                                87</ref>.</note> and 7138, September 1, 8 p.m.,<note n="90" xml:id="d58fn90">
                                <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_329">p.
                                329</ref>.</note> the Department is prepared to meet the request of
                            the French National Committee of Liberation for an opportunity to
                            consult with the EAC on those questions directly affecting French
                            interests.</p>
                        <p>Accordingly you are authorized to agree to the submission to the
                            representatives of the French National Committee of Liberation of the
                            text of the instrument of unconditional surrender for Germany<note n="91" xml:id="d58fn91">For text of the Instrument of Surrender for
                                Germany, see <ref target="#pg_256">p. 256</ref>.</note> and to an
                            invitation to the French to consult with the Commission with regard to
                            the surrender terms and other questions arising from them.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>